text:
A followup to my question re: checking for monotonicity (<https://julialang.slack.com/archives/C6A044SQH/p1610033087464400>):

Is there perhaps an efficient way to use iterators in order to get a penalty function for monotonicity breaks? E.g.
```x = [1.5 3.4 3.0 4.0]
function linearDevPenalty(x)
   penalty = 0
   for i = i:(length(x) - 1)
      penalty += max(x[i] - x[i+1], 0)
   end
return(penalty)
end```

